commit.message:
Fix various small bugs and edge-cases

- cmake.yml: Update versions of GitHub actions.
- aff_data.cxx: Fix edge case when parsing LONG flags (two chars) when the
  char value is above 127/less than 0/above ASCII. In the cases where C++
  char is signed, such chars are negative, the bitwise operation did not
  really worked properly. This was mostly theoretical bug as the few
  dictionaries that use LONG flags do not use chars above 127 for flags.
- aff_data.hxx: Make the class Aff_Data usable with default initialization
  by adding default initializers to all members. This class is aggregate
  which means that it was properly initialized in both value-initialization
  `auto x = Aff_Data()` and aggregate-initialization `Aff_Data x = {}`.
  It was not properly initialized with default-initialization. This was not
  a bug because that initialization was never used with this class.

  Silence some compiler warnings about call to std::move being unqualified.
- checker.hxx: See above about Aff_Data initialization.
- dictionary.cxx: silence compiler warnings about std::move. Remove header.
- structures.hxx: likewise.
- suggester.cxx: likewise.
- utils.cxx: remove unused header.
Prepare version 5.1.4

Use Catch2 v3 for unit tests

Fixes #133
Prepare version 5.1.3

Improve the handling of dependencies in CMake

Use FetchContent for pulling the dependency Catch2 in CMake instead of
submodules. The new logic first tries find_package() and if that fails,
it uses the CMake's module FetchContent. The module is very flexible, it
downloads the dependency's source code from the Internet, but even allows
one to specify custom source directory to avoid downloading, which might be
needed in some environments that require fully offline builds. Although,
such environments should probably use the find_package() method and just
install Catch2 before building Nuspell.

Simplify the generating of the pkg-config file

Modernize usage of Vcpkg in CI

Use Vcpkg's manifest mode.

Put the inline namespace definition with preprocessor definition

This helps doxygen to not see the inline namespace.
Additionally it is easier to update it, because it is at only one place.
Update copyright years

Prepare version 5.1.2

Additionaly, fix CI on Windows.
Improve performance of suggestions.

Improve testing tool verify to work with suggestions

1. Implement logic for measuring quality of suggestions by using
   Wikipedia's list of common misspellings
2. Delete similar old tests.
3. Add more fine-grained time measurements.
Rewrite testing tool verify

Fix CLI tool about encoding issue on Windows

When reading file instead of STDIN on Windows, make the default encoding UTF-8.

Additionally, optimize the creation of out_ucnv object. When input and
output encoding are same, make out_ucnv the same (alias) with in_ucnv
instead of creating a new one.
Prepare version 5.1.1
Apply clang-format

Improve error-reporting, no more direct usage of cerr.

The library does not use directly any of the standard stream object like
cerr anymore. Instead, in Aff_Parser, any ostream object can be injected
that receives the error message. In the class Dictionary the functions
for loading the dictionary throw as usual but now have much richer error
message. So, now the library does not pollute cout or cerr and it is up
to the user to print the error message via the exception.

Additional function for loading has been added in class Dictionary (only
for internal use) that receives ostream object for error messages.

In the executable CLI tool std::clog is used everywhere instead of
std::cerr and explicit flushes with std::endl are used where needed.

Refactor parsing in Aff_Data

No more overloading of operator>>. Code is cleaner to read now.

Improve error reporting in Aff_Data

Errors and warnings have more details.

Add support for getopt on Windows + MSVC

The package is available in vcpkg.

Additionally:
- Add configuration option BUILD_TOOLS that can be used to disable
  building the CLI tool. It is ON by default.
- Modernize calls to target_link_libraries() in CMake to include the
  keyword PRIVATE where needed.

Use tabs for indentation in CMake files.

At few places spaces are used for further alignment.
This change harmonizes with the C++ code whitch also uses tabs.

Update CI, update Catch2 submodule.

Don't use Catch2 v3 via vcpkg, use v2 via submodule on Windows.
Fix compiler warning. Update README.
Prepare changelog for new release v5.1.0

Improve the searching for dictionaries on the filesystem.

- Expose new API with std::filesystem::path
- Deprecate API that store paths in std::string
- Faster, see search_dirs_for_one_dict()

Refactor dictionary finder using C++17 std::filesystem

There are some improvements in append_libreoffice_dir_paths(), mostly for
Windows.
Update copyright years
Simplify CLI tool
Fix and improve caching on CI
Prepare version v5.0.1
Update CI provider, use Github Actions.
